Omotola Jalade Ekeinde’s son, Captain E, has been nominated for a music award. According to details available to The Nation, Captain E has been nominated for the 25Under25 Music Category Award. Sometimes in June 2020, Captain E released new music weeks after Omotola announced her readiness to embrace music again. The singer and producer released his second single in 2020 after promising to keep dishing out more music in 2020. Entitled ‘craze,’ the new song was released earlier in the week. According to a terse statement from Captain E, the new song talks about a never-ending cycle of a modern toxic relationship. The new single is coming a few weeks after the release of ‘You & I’ in May 2020.